dfcols = ['App Name','Method Name', 'Usage', 'Arguments','Type']
df_Community_Malicious = pd.DataFrame(columns=dfcols)
for fileName in fileNames:
    
    appName = fileName[:fileName.index('.')].strip()
    with open(("sorted_apps\\community\\malicious\\"+fileName), 'r') as text:
        i = 0
        dictSink = {}
        for line in text.readlines():
            if (line[:14].strip() == "Data Flow Path"):
                break        

            if((len(line.split(':'))<2) and (len(line.strip())>0)):
                #print(line)
                dictSink['App Name'] = appName
                dictSink["Type"] = 'Sink'
                dictSink["Usage"] = line.strip()

            if(line.split(':')[0].strip() == 'Method Name'):
                #print(line)
                dictSink[line.split(':')[0].strip()] = line.split(':')[1].split(' ')[1].strip()
                #print(i,dictSink,' __ ',line)

            if(line.split(':')[0].strip() == 'Arguments'):
                #print(line)
                #if I use a simple split on ':' to read argument and its value it does not read
                #the whole argument is not read in the cases like 'Arguments: ($decodedString, [method:push])'
                #dictSink[line.split(':')[0].strip()] = line.split(':')[1].split(' ')[1].strip()
                dictSink[line[:line.index(':')].strip()] = line[line.index(':')+1:].strip()
                #print(i,dictSink,' __ ',line)

                df_Community_Malicious = df_Community_Malicious.append(dictSink,ignore_index=True)
                dictSink = {}

            #i = i+1
            #print(i)
df_Community_Malicious

colNames = ['App_Name','Type','Category','numSinks', 'sendNotification', 'sendNotificationToContacts', 'sendPush', 'sendSms'
            , 'httpGet', 'httpPostJson', 'httpPost', 'httpPut', 'httpDelete', 'httpPutJson']

df_Community_Malicious_Sinks = pd.DataFrame(columns=colNames)
for fileName in fileNames:
    
    appName = fileName[:fileName.index('.')].strip()
    with open(("sorted_apps\\community\\malicious\\"+fileName), 'r') as text:
        i = 0        
        dictSink = {'App_Name':'','numSinks':0, 'sendNotification':0, 'sendNotificationToContacts':0, 'sendPush':0, 'sendSms':0, 'httpGet':0, 
 'httpPostJson':0, 'httpPost':0, 'httpPut':0, 'httpDelete':0, 'httpPutJson':0}
        dictSink['App_Name'] = appName
        dictSink['Type'] = 'Malicious'
        dictSink['Category'] = 'Community'
        for line in text.readlines():
            if (line[:14].strip() == "Data Flow Path"):
                dictSink[line.split('-->')[1].strip()] = dictSink[line.split('-->')[1].strip()]+1
                dictSink['numSinks'] = dictSink['numSinks']+1
                
        df_Community_Malicious_Sinks = df_Community_Malicious_Sinks.append(dictSink,ignore_index=True)
        dictSink = {}

summaryCols = ['App_Name','SMSsSent','notificationsSent', 'internetUsed']
df_Community_Malicious_Summary = pd.DataFrame(columns=summaryCols)
for fileName in fileNames:    
    appName = fileName[:fileName.index('.')].strip()
    
    with open(("sorted_apps\\community\\malicious\\"+fileName), 'r') as text: 
        
        dictSumSink = {}
        dictSumSink['App_Name'] = appName
        #for optimised parsing reversed the order of lines. 
        #The data that I'm interested in is at the end of the file
        for line in list(reversed(text.readlines())):                           

            #print(line)
            if(':' in line):
                if (line[:line.index(':')].strip() == "Total times using internet"):
                    dictSumSink["internetUsed"] = line.split(':')[1].strip()            
            
            if(':' in line):
                if (line[:line.index(':')].strip() == "Total times sending notifications"):
                    dictSumSink["notificationsSent"] = line.split(':')[1].strip()
           
            if(':' in line):                
                if (line[:line.index(':')].strip() == "Total times sending SMSs or messages"):
                    dictSumSink["SMSsSent"] = line.split(':')[1].strip()
                    break
        df_Community_Malicious_Summary = df_Community_Malicious_Summary.append(dictSumSink,ignore_index=True)
        df_SumSinks = {}

summaryCols = ['App_Name','SMSsSent','notificationsSent', 'internetUsed']
df_Forum_Malicious_Summary = pd.DataFrame(columns=summaryCols)
for fileName in fileNames:    
    appName = fileName[:fileName.index('.')].strip()
    
    with open(("sorted_apps\\forum\\malicious\\"+fileName), 'r') as text: 
        
        dictSumSink = {}
        dictSumSink['App_Name'] = appName
        #for optimised parsing reversed the order of lines. 
        #The data that I'm interested in is at the end of the file
        for line in list(reversed(text.readlines())):                           

            #print(line)
            if(':' in line):
                if (line[:line.index(':')].strip() == "Total times using internet"):
                    dictSumSink["internetUsed"] = line.split(':')[1].strip()            
            
            if(':' in line):
                if (line[:line.index(':')].strip() == "Total times sending notifications"):
                    dictSumSink["notificationsSent"] = line.split(':')[1].strip()
           
            if(':' in line):                
                if (line[:line.index(':')].strip() == "Total times sending SMSs or messages"):
                    dictSumSink["SMSsSent"] = line.split(':')[1].strip()
                    break
        df_Forum_Malicious_Summary = df_Forum_Malicious_Summary.append(dictSumSink,ignore_index=True)
        df_SumSinks = {}

summaryCols = ['App_Name','SMSsSent','notificationsSent', 'internetUsed']
df_Forum_Benign_Summary = pd.DataFrame(columns=summaryCols)
for fileName in fileNames:    
    appName = fileName[:fileName.index('.')].strip()
    
    with open(("sorted_apps\\forum\\benign\\"+fileName), 'r') as text: 
        
        dictSumSink = {}
        dictSumSink['App_Name'] = appName
        #for optimised parsing reversed the order of lines. 
        #The data that I'm interested in is at the end of the file
        for line in list(reversed(text.readlines())):                           

            #print(line)
            if(':' in line):
                if (line[:line.index(':')].strip() == "Total times using internet"):
                    dictSumSink["internetUsed"] = line.split(':')[1].strip()            
            
            if(':' in line):
                if (line[:line.index(':')].strip() == "Total times sending notifications"):
                    dictSumSink["notificationsSent"] = line.split(':')[1].strip()
           
            if(':' in line):                
                if (line[:line.index(':')].strip() == "Total times sending SMSs or messages"):
                    dictSumSink["SMSsSent"] = line.split(':')[1].strip()
                    break
        df_Forum_Benign_Summary = df_Forum_Benign_Summary.append(dictSumSink,ignore_index=True)
        df_SumSinks = {}

summaryCols = ['App_Name','SMSsSent','notificationsSent', 'internetUsed']
df_Saint_Benign_Summary = pd.DataFrame(columns=summaryCols)
for fileName in fileNames:    
    appName = fileName[:fileName.index('.')].strip()
    
    with open(("sorted_apps\\saint\\benign\\"+fileName), 'r') as text: 
        
        dictSumSink = {}
        dictSumSink['App_Name'] = appName
        #for optimised parsing reversed the order of lines. 
        #The data that I'm interested in is at the end of the file
        for line in list(reversed(text.readlines())):                           

            #print(line)
            if(':' in line):
                if (line[:line.index(':')].strip() == "Total times using internet"):
                    dictSumSink["internetUsed"] = line.split(':')[1].strip()            
            
            if(':' in line):
                if (line[:line.index(':')].strip() == "Total times sending notifications"):
                    dictSumSink["notificationsSent"] = line.split(':')[1].strip()
           
            if(':' in line):                
                if (line[:line.index(':')].strip() == "Total times sending SMSs or messages"):
                    dictSumSink["SMSsSent"] = line.split(':')[1].strip()
                    break
        df_Saint_Benign_Summary = df_Saint_Benign_Summary.append(dictSumSink,ignore_index=True)
        df_SumSinks = {}

Logistic Regression¶

In [82]:
objLG = LogisticRegression()
objLG.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_pred = objLG.predict(X_test)
In [83]:
faceLabels = ['Benign','Malicious']
mat = metrics.confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
sns.heatmap(mat.T, square=True, annot=True, fmt='d', cbar=False,
            xticklabels = faceLabels, cmap="BuPu", linecolor='black', linewidths=1,
            yticklabels = faceLabels)
plt.xlabel('true label')
plt.ylabel('predicted label');
plt.title('Confusion Matrix Logistic Regression')
plt.show()
In [84]:
print("Accuracy : ",metrics.accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))
print(metrics.classification_report(y_test, y_pred))
